MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. (AP) _ Confluent Inc. (CFLT) on Thursday reported a loss of $113 million in its first quarter.On a per-share basis, the Mountain View, California-based company said it had a loss of 41 cents. Losses, adjusted for stock option expense and amortization costs, were 19 cents per share.The results topped Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of eight analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for a loss of 21 cents per share.The data infrastructure software maker posted revenue of $126.1 million in the period, also exceeding Street forecasts. Seven analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $118.5 million.For the current quarter ending in July, Confluent expects its results to range from a loss of 21 cents per share to a loss of 19 cents per share.The company said it expects revenue in the range of $130 million to $132 million for the fiscal second quarter.ADVERTISEMENTConfluent expects full-year results to range from a loss of 79 cents per share to a loss of 73 cents per share, with revenue ranging from $554 million to $560 million.Confluent shares have dropped 63% since the beginning of the year.BusinessStocks slump 3% as worries grow over higher interest ratesMajor companies stay mum on thorny abortion issue - for nowRising interest rates in US will hinder foreign economiesSmall businesses still struggle to find enough workers_____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on CFLT at https://www.zacks.com/ap/CFLT